  "notes": "Par-68 Nicklaus Design course (six par 3s, front and back both par 34). Hole data (par, hcp, per-hole meters, Vc/Vs per tee and gender) taken from the official RFEG club page. Cross-checked with golfingholiday.com scorecard (yards): pars identical and all per-hole yardages convert exactly to RFEG meters (totals 5909/5447/4929/4248 yd = 5403/4981/4507/3884 m); golfshake totals and white-tee men's slope (128) also agree. Discrepancy: golfingholiday shows a different stroke-index allocation (e.g. SI 1 on hole 10, SI 2 on hole 2); the RFEG men's handicap allocation (SI 1 = hole 2, SI 2 = hole 10, etc.) is used here as authoritative. Golfshake's older SSS/slope figures for yellow/blue/red differ slightly from current RFEG ratings; RFEG values are used. All four tees are rated for both genders, so each appears twice with identical distances."
